// @test regression/INV078-invalid-operator-statement
// @description A statement cannot start with a binary/ternary/colon operator. TV reports CE10156 "new line" at the operator line, while unary +/- and not expression tails remain valid. Probed 2026-06-20; see investigations/INV078-invalid-operator-statement/notes.md.
// @expects parse: fail
// @expects errors: 3
// @expects error: line=4, column=1, message=/Syntax error at input "new line"/
// @expects error: line=6, column=5, message=/Syntax error at input "new line"/
// @expects error: line=8, column=5, message=/Syntax error at input "new line"/
//@version=6
indicator("INV078")
x = close
? high : low
f() =>
    and high
badColon() =>
    : high
validUnary() =>
    -high
validNot() =>
    not close
plot(close)
